I am creating custom macros that require connecting to application link servers. For this, the user needs to select the Server to connect to. 

Please create a new macro parameter option type of "server" that displays a select field with a list of application link names and applinkIds as values.

Note: Some macros require the user to select a JIRA project (CONF-37573), other macros do NOT need the JIRA project.

*Steps to reproduce:*
# Create a page PageA
# Create a child page -PageB under pageA
## Add a header {noformat}{h1}Foo{/h1}{noformat}
## Add a children-display macro
# Create a child page PageC under pageB
## Add a header {noformat}{h1}Bar{/h1}{noformat}
# Edit pageA, add table of content zone macro
## Add a include-page macro in table of content zone macro
## Include PageB inside the include page macro
{code}
PageA
{toc-zone}{include-page PageB}{/toc-zone}
- PageB
{h1}Foo{/h1}
{children-display/}
-- PageC
{h1}Bar{/h1}
{code}

*Expected result*
!tablecontentzone.PNG|thumbnail!

