As of now, when a user tries to upload a corrupted image to a Confluence page, a general error message would then be shown on the 'Insert files and images' popup. 
{noformat}
Error retrieving attachments from Confluence. The server may be unavailable.
{noformat}

Given the user wasn't aware that the image is corrupted, they would then try to reupload the affected image for a number of times, which could then lead to OutOfMemory error mentioned in [CONF-34076|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-34076] that hangs the _Insert files and images_ feature.

It would be better if Confluence can provide a more specific error message, so the user could have a clearer idea of what's causing the error without even have to look at the logs, as not every Confluence users will have access to the logs. 








