Confluence could give an option to disable the File Versioning.

Confluence is often used by software development teams, which may be using it for debugging or troubleshooting. In that case, posting multiple versions of the same output file would be common and it may be important to preserve the location of each file on the page relative to various comments and text also on the page. In that case, the auto-versioning (which is wonderful in other situations) creates a real problem.

